00:53.178 --> 00:54.971
And it's <i>50,000</i>

00:55.055 --> 00:57.390
that I'm <i>not </i> asking you for, not 15, okay?

00:57.474 --> 00:59.434
Which I could probably lend you.

00:59.517 --> 01:02.103
- Oh, I don't need it.
- Huh? No? Good. Yeah?

01:02.187 --> 01:03.646
Good, good.

01:03.730 --> 01:05.815
So your Fakeblock's doing well?

01:05.899 --> 01:08.109
<i>George Michael had been</i>
<i>looking for an opportunity</i>

01:08.193 --> 01:10.153
<i>to come clean about Fakeblock...</i>

01:10.236 --> 01:12.739
- Been meaning to ask.
<i>- ...but this wasn't it.</i>

01:12.822 --> 01:15.825
Yeah, well, Fakeblock's money is
all tied up in legalities,

01:15.909 --> 01:17.911
- patenting, marketing.
- Sounds amazing.

01:18.036 --> 01:20.163
Good for you, good for you. Good for him.

01:20.246 --> 01:21.915
We're trying to figure out
the Buster thing.

01:21.998 --> 01:25.668
Well, if we can't use the company money
to get Buster out,

01:25.752 --> 01:28.004
you better figure out a way to do it,
Barry...

01:29.422 --> 01:30.924
or I'll use my own lawyer.

01:31.007 --> 01:33.510
What are you talking about,
another lawyer?

01:33.593 --> 01:35.804
You don't have the courtesy to wait
until I'm disbarred?

01:35.887 --> 01:38.640
Is this a divorce guy? Oh, this hurts.

01:38.723 --> 01:40.517
Give me a second, I'll be all right.

01:40.600 --> 01:43.311
I was gonna use your divorce
to pay off my peekaboo lawyer.

01:43.394 --> 01:46.106
His name is Dustin Radler,
and I haven't hired him,

01:46.189 --> 01:48.942
because technically,
he's given up the rat race.

01:49.025 --> 01:51.152
Oh, God, the giving up the rat race guy?

01:51.236 --> 01:52.570
This is the sand hobo?

01:52.654 --> 01:54.030
Uh, it's just a question.

01:54.114 --> 01:55.865
Are you guys doing something?

01:55.949 --> 01:57.492
Don't say it!

01:57.575 --> 02:00.537
Please, I can't... I can't hear it.

02:00.620 --> 02:02.455
He tickles my fancy.

02:02.539 --> 02:04.582
Your what? Is the...

02:04.666 --> 02:07.460
What part of Mom is the fancy?

02:07.544 --> 02:09.336
You do not want to know
what I'm picturing,

02:09.419 --> 02:11.381
and it's not what you think.

02:11.464 --> 02:12.841
Oh, stop.

02:12.924 --> 02:14.217
We walk on the beach.

02:14.300 --> 02:16.803
We like the feel
of the sand on our feet.

02:16.886 --> 02:19.013
Oh, God, the thought of your feet.

02:19.097 --> 02:20.306
It's fine.

02:20.390 --> 02:21.933
I'm glad you have someone to talk to.

02:22.016 --> 02:24.310
Well, maybe I'll go check on Buster.

02:24.394 --> 02:26.980
Wow.
Mom really has him fancy-whipped, huh?

02:27.063 --> 02:29.607
You don't want to bring another lawyer
into this.

02:29.691 --> 02:32.527
You don't want to go in fully armed,
because the DA,

02:32.610 --> 02:34.863
she's up for reelection,
and she's a killer.

02:34.946 --> 02:36.573
God, I even hate to say her name.

02:38.199 --> 02:40.535
Yeah, Lottie Dottie DA, my asshole.

02:40.618 --> 02:44.706
Okay. When it comes to Buster:
a total press blackout.

02:45.165 --> 02:47.167
Couldn't agree more.
We have to be diligent.

02:47.250 --> 02:48.668
- No media.
- Uh...

02:49.419 --> 02:51.838
are we talking about reality or, uh,

02:51.921 --> 02:54.382
scripted, as well,
because I've got...

02:54.465 --> 02:56.968
Why would there be a scripted
about the family?

02:57.051 --> 02:59.220
Weren't you working on one
with Ron Howard?

03:02.348 --> 03:04.142
You're saying
that's not grandfathered in.

03:05.518 --> 03:06.853
'Cause it was before the murder.

03:06.936 --> 03:08.438
Michael, tell me that movie

03:08.521 --> 03:12.066
you were producing about us
is not still happening.

03:12.150 --> 03:14.360
I do not think that it is. I mean, I...

03:14.444 --> 03:17.906
I gave the releases to Kitty,
but the industry does not move fast.

03:17.989 --> 03:20.950
Well, then, talk to Kitty
and get them back.

03:21.034 --> 03:22.535
Can't. Kitty hates me.

03:23.536 --> 03:25.288
Did you catch this?

03:25.705 --> 03:27.123
Man, that's priceless.

03:27.207 --> 03:29.042
First, you eat it with Buster,

03:29.375 --> 03:31.127
then you step in it with the movie,

03:31.211 --> 03:33.087
and now you're eating
what you stepped in,

03:33.171 --> 03:35.590
because Kitty hates you.

03:36.674 --> 03:39.344
Guess Michael's the geo-bead today.

03:40.011 --> 03:41.304
Did you say "geo-bead"?

03:41.387 --> 03:44.974
Yeah, it's one of Dad's expressions...
When somebody screws up, Dad said it.

03:45.058 --> 03:47.518
One of his "you'll figure it out
someday" expressions.

03:47.602 --> 03:49.187
- Okay.
- Know what? You're lucky,

03:49.270 --> 03:51.606
'cause Kitty's sweet on me,
so I'll go with you.

03:51.689 --> 03:54.442
- No, thank you. Nope.
- I could go. Or just...

03:54.525 --> 03:58.321
Would that be helpful if I did?
Or am I just being a G-O-B?

03:58.404 --> 03:59.656
Uh...

03:59.739 --> 04:01.783
G-O-B spells "Gob," you geo-bead,

04:01.866 --> 04:03.201
so why don't you s... ah.

04:04.327 --> 04:05.662
Well, today's the day.

04:05.745 --> 04:08.706
Why are you even still here?
Go find your wife.

04:10.083 --> 04:11.417
I don't know where she is.

04:11.960 --> 04:13.586
Well, track down the ex-boyfriend.

04:13.670 --> 04:15.255
And take Tonto with you.

04:15.338 --> 04:17.673
Yes, of course, Marky Bark.

04:18.007 --> 04:19.384
From the cuckolding.

04:19.466 --> 04:23.221
I think I might have an idea
of where I can, I think.

04:23.346 --> 04:24.430
- Come on!
- Coming!

04:24.514 --> 04:27.558
<i>And as Tobias rushed off</i>
<i>with his newfound son,</i>

04:27.642 --> 04:29.477
<i>George Michael and his cousin</i>

04:29.560 --> 04:31.729
<i>- caught up.</i>
<i>- </i> I can't believe this is the third

04:31.813 --> 04:33.731
"welcome home from prison" party
we've thrown.

